Reasoning: The claim is supported by evidence from paper ID 205268782, titled "Adjuvant whole-brain radiation therapy after surgical resection of single brain metastases." This retrospective study of 358 patients found that Whole Brain Radiation Therapy (WBRT) significantly reduced distant brain site recurrence (HR = 0.43, 95% CI 0.30-0.61, P < .001). The abstract further states that "Adjuvant WBRT significantly reduces local and distant recurrences in subsets of patients, particularly those with metastases >3 cm or with active systemic disease." This directly indicates that WBRT reduces the occurrence of new brain metastases. While the study is retrospective and more corroborating evidence from other high-quality studies would increase confidence, the findings are clear and directly relevant to the claim.
